tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE user_interactions (
  user_id INT,
  interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
  interaction_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  interaction_duration INT,
  PRIMARY KEY (user_id, interaction_timestamp)
);

CREATE TABLE engagement_metrics (
  metric_id INT,
  user_id INT,
  engagement_score FLOAT,
  timestamp DATE,
  PRIMARY KEY (metric_id)
);

CREATE TABLE courses (
    course_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    course_name VARCHAR(100),
    instructor VARCHAR(50),
    created_at TIMESTAMP,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE interactions (
    interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    course_id INT,
    interaction_type VARCHAR(20),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (course_id) REFERENCES courses(course_id)
);

CREATE TABLE user_interactions (
  interaction_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT REFERENCES users(user_id),
  course_id INT REFERENCES courses(course_id),
  timestamp TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
  interaction_type VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE user_interactions (
    user_id INT,
    interaction_type VARCHAR,
    interaction_time TIMESTAMP,
    interaction_content TEXT,
    PRIMARY KEY (user_id, interaction_time)
)

CREATE TABLE user_details (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR,
    email VARCHAR,
    registration_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE course_interactions (
    course_id INT,
    user_id INT,
    interaction_type VARCHAR,
    interaction_time TIMESTAMP,
    PRIMARY KEY (course_id, user_id, interaction_time)
)

CREATE TABLE course_details (
    course_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    course_name VARCHAR,
    instructor VARCHAR,
    start_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE engagement_metrics (
    user_id INT,
    course_id INT,
    time_on_course INTERVAL,
    assignments_completed INT,
    quizzes_completed INT,
    progress_percentage FLOAT,
    PRIMARY KEY (user_id, course_id)
)
